üìù Objective:
Use basic CSS styling properties to design layout components using:
- color
- background-color
- border
- height
- width
- background (image, repeat, size, etc.)

üìÇ Instructions:
1. Create an HTML file and link a CSS file.
2. Complete the following design tasks using only CSS.
3. Use external or internal styles only (avoid inline styles).
4. Add comments in your CSS to mark each task.

TASK SOLUTION-

basic.html:-

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>CSS Styling Example</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <div class="box">Colored Box</div>
  <div class="background-box">Background Image Box</div>
</body>
</html>



style.css:-


/* Task 1: Set text color */
.box {
  color: white; /* text color */
  
  /* Task 2: Set background color */
  background-color: teal;

  /* Task 3: Add border */
  border: 3px solid black;

  /* Task 4: Set height and width */
  width: 300px;
  height: 150px;

  /* Center content */
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;

  margin: 20px auto;
  font-size: 20px;
}

/* Task 5: Set background image with repeat, size, and positioning */
.background-box {
  background-image: url('https://via.placeholder.com/300x150');
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: center;

  width: 300px;
  height: 150px;

  border: 2px dashed gray;

  margin: 20px auto;
}
